snippet: Iceland has withdrawn its bid to join the European Union, with the government saying its interests are best served outside the 28-nation bloc, a spokeswoman for the European Union said Friday.
lead_paragraph: Iceland has withdrawn its bid to join the European Union, with the government saying its interests are best served outside the 28-nation bloc, a spokeswoman for the European Union said Friday.

headline.main: Iceland: No Longer Eager to Join E.U.
